================================================================================
3. THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
================================================================================

WaveShaper incorporates the following open-source libraries:

NAudio 2.2.1 - Licensed under MIT
A comprehensive .NET audio library for file decoding, real-time playback,
WASAPI/DirectSound audio device communication and sample processing.
Website: https://github.com/naudio/NAudio

NAudio.Lame 2.1.0 - Licensed under MIT (LAME is LGPL)
Enables high-quality MP3 encoding through the LAME encoder for audio export.
Website: https://github.com/Corey-M/NAudio.Lame

SoundTouch.Net 2.3.2 - Licensed under LGPL v2.1
A .NET wrapper for the SoundTouch audio processing library, powering time
stretching and pitch shifting features.
Website: https://www.surina.net/soundtouch/

TagLibSharp 2.3.0 - Licensed under LGPL
Handles audio metadata operations, allowing reading and writing of file tags
such as title, artist and album information.
Website: https://github.com/mono/taglib-sharp

Newtonsoft.Json 13.0.4 - Licensed under MIT
Provides JSON serialization for settings, preset files and configuration
management throughout the application.
Website: https://www.newtonsoft.com/json

Users should review and comply with the licensing terms of these components.

================================================================================
4. DATA HANDLING
================================================================================

WaveShaper uses a shared account system with Medio. Only minimal data is stored
on the server, while all settings and audio data remain local on your device.

WHAT WAVESHAPER STORES ON THE SERVER:

  - Progress: Experience points and level (updated after each export)
  - Avatar: Your profile image (if uploaded)
  - License: Current license type and activation status

WHAT WAVESHAPER STORES LOCALLY:

  - Settings: EQ preferences, effect parameters, export configuration
  - Presets: Custom EQ presets and effect configurations
  - History: Recent projects, downloads and export history
  - Project library: Imported audio file references

WHAT WAVESHAPER DOES NOT STORE:

  - Names, emails, addresses, or phone numbers
  - Payment information (handled securely by Stripe)
  - The actual content of processed audio files
  - Your file system activity outside of WaveShaper
  - Settings or preferences on the server (all local)

PRIVACY CONTROLS:

You have control over your data:

  - Delete individual history entries via right-click context menus
  - Unlink your account via the application menu
  - Factory reset to remove all local settings and data

DATA RETENTION:

  - Basic accounts: Automatically deleted after 365 days of inactivity
  - Premium accounts: Retained while license is active

